WEBVTT

00:46.255 --> 00:48.675
911, what's your emergency?

01:18.328 --> 01:19.747
Hands in the air!
Let me see your hands!

01:32.802 --> 01:35.472
7435.

01:50.528 --> 01:53.280
Okay, Aiden.

01:53.363 --> 01:54.990
Let's start.

01:55.073 --> 01:56.742
Tell us what happened.

02:05.585 --> 02:06.837
Hey, Melissa.

02:07.753 --> 02:08.588
You’re in trouble.

02:08.672 --> 02:10.005
They already started.

02:11.007 --> 02:13.467
Okay, so let's remember,
we have two types of readers.

02:13.552 --> 02:15.262
Readers who are wearing
these labels

02:15.345 --> 02:17.138
and readers who aspire
to wear these labels.

02:17.222 --> 02:18.263
AIDEN:
Sorry.

02:19.390 --> 02:20.808
Sorry, I'm late.

02:20.892 --> 02:22.268
As I was saying, that
Fashion East article

02:22.352 --> 02:23.435
was a good one.

02:23.520 --> 02:25.813
But let's not refer to that
one from New York.

02:25.897 --> 02:28.398
Um, what's her name?

02:29.483 --> 02:30.652
Anna Wintour?

02:30.735 --> 02:32.362
MICHAEL:
Yes, Anna Wintour!

02:32.445 --> 02:35.030
Avoid things like that
and we should be fine.

02:35.113 --> 02:38.910
Okay, moving on
to our next item.

02:38.993 --> 02:40.828
Something we've all been
waiting for.

02:40.912 --> 02:43.080
Something we've all worked
very hard for.

02:44.415 --> 02:46.833
Zelia is ours!

02:46.918 --> 02:48.418
Yes!

02:49.128 --> 02:50.170
Yes, oh my God.

02:50.255 --> 02:51.838
I don't have to tell you
how big this is for us.

02:51.923 --> 02:53.423
You all know very well.

02:53.507 --> 02:56.427
So, I'll be handing over
her account to our best.

02:59.555 --> 03:00.890
Daniel...

03:02.725 --> 03:04.310
...Zelia is yours.

03:06.145 --> 03:06.938
Oh!

03:07.022 --> 03:08.773
Oh, that's great!

03:08.857 --> 03:10.275
Thank you,
thank you, Michael.

03:10.358 --> 03:12.235
We'll meet this afternoon,
chart out a strategy.

03:12.318 --> 03:12.985
Yeah, yeah.

03:13.068 --> 03:14.778
-Abso-- absolutely.
-Okay.

03:14.862 --> 03:16.072
Okay.

03:16.155 --> 03:17.407
Alright, I wanna hear some
ideas about next month's issue.

03:26.790 --> 03:29.127
So, that meeting...

03:29.210 --> 03:31.587
...who's Zelia?

03:31.670 --> 03:33.172
Seriously?

03:33.255 --> 03:35.258
You are interning here

03:35.342 --> 03:38.260
and you don't know
who Zelia is?

03:39.553 --> 03:40.805
She's Toronto's hope for a real
legitimate standing

03:40.888 --> 03:42.223
in the fashion world!

03:43.808 --> 03:45.768
Okay, so you know we have fashion week

03:45.852 --> 03:47.270
every year here, right?

03:47.353 --> 03:51.273
Well, every year Zelia releases
her new collection here,

03:51.357 --> 03:54.610
instead of in London
or Paris or even New York.

03:54.693 --> 03:56.445
And every year people come
from all over

03:56.528 --> 03:58.698
just to see her new line.

03:58.782 --> 04:00.533
And if she keeps going the way
that she is,

04:00.617 --> 04:02.535
then those same designers
may wanna stay

04:02.618 --> 04:05.705
and compete with her here,
in Toronto.

04:05.788 --> 04:07.332
Okay.

04:07.415 --> 04:09.542
Well, that’d be good,
right?

04:09.625 --> 04:10.960
Yeah.

04:12.212 --> 04:13.170
Get back to work.

04:14.172 --> 04:15.548
SOPHIA:
Here.

04:15.632 --> 04:17.550
Take this to Maggie's office,
intern.

04:19.385 --> 04:21.637
It's uh, Aiden, actually.

04:21.720 --> 04:23.472
Oh, really?

04:33.232 --> 04:35.902
MAGGIE:
Sleeping around has its
benefits, right Daniel?

04:35.985 --> 04:36.987
What the hell, Maggie.

04:37.070 --> 04:40.155
I got the Zelia's account
because I'm good.

04:40.238 --> 04:43.033
I'm sure the boss' niece
would agree with you.

04:44.702 --> 04:45.787
Screw you, Maggie!

05:23.992 --> 05:25.242
MAGGIE:
What?

05:26.827 --> 05:27.912
What are you--

05:27.995 --> 05:28.913
Maggie.

05:28.997 --> 05:30.288
Have you see Daniel?

05:30.373 --> 05:31.373
No, I haven't.

05:31.457 --> 05:32.750
He must be on a smoke break.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.168
Okay, okay.

05:34.252 --> 05:35.712
Oh!

05:35.795 --> 05:37.213
Look at that!

05:37.297 --> 05:38.923
Made some adjustments
to the layout

05:39.007 --> 05:39.757
and colour palette.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.175
Oh, I--

05:41.258 --> 05:42.927
It's good, it's good.

05:43.010 --> 05:43.677
Thanks.

05:43.762 --> 05:45.262
Michael, do you have a minute?

05:45.345 --> 05:47.098
Yeah, sure what's up?

05:47.182 --> 05:48.767
The Zelia account.

05:48.850 --> 05:50.100
MICHAEL:
Alright.

05:50.183 --> 05:52.853
We're all trying to make this
the best magazine possible.

05:52.937 --> 05:54.605
So, I made the decision.

05:54.688 --> 05:56.440
Do you understand?

05:56.523 --> 05:58.192
Thanks.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.082
-Hey.
-Hey.

06:12.165 --> 06:14.417
